INSERT INTO `c_documentation` VALUES (159,'<p>1.    Single Header Form – One table though form – rest _after_save()<br />Form with a single header and no lines. Primary data stored in a single table.<br />Ex : Path, Content, Page, WIP Move Transaction, Category<br />1.1    Single header with data in line tab – <br />BOM Resource, Enterprise, Business Org, Cost Type, Material Element<br />1.2 Single header with data in line tab /header tab  - Item Master<br /><br />2.    Multiple Lines of single form<br />Forms without header but multiple lines<br />Ex :  Calaendar, Transaction Type, Sub inventory,  Inventory Transaction, WIP WO Transaction, UOM, Locator, Receipts<br /><br />3.    One header – One Line – two forms<br />Forms with one header and one line displayed at a time<br />Ex: Supplier, Customer<br /><br />4.    One header – Multiple Line – two forms<br />Forms with one header and multiple lines <br />Ex: Content Type, Role Path, User, BOM, Standard Operation, Value Group, WIP Resource Transactions<br /><br />5.    One header – Multiple Line with details – two forms<br />Forms with one header and multiple lines <br />Ex : Options, PO, SO, Routing, WO<br /><br />6.    3 different forms<br />Ex: Payment term, Over Head, Departments</p>','CONTENT'),(160,'<pre>    [0] => coa_combination_id\r\n    [1] => coa_id\r\n    [2] => field1\r\n    [3] => field2\r\n    [4] => field3\r\n    [5] => field4\r\n    [6] => field5\r\n    [7] => field6\r\n    [8] => field7\r\n    [9] => field8\r\n    [10] => combination\r\n    [11] => description\r\n    [12] => ef_id\r\n    [13] => status\r\n    [14] => rev_enabled\r\n    [15] => rev_number\r\n    [16] => effective_start_date\r\n    [17] => effective_end_date\r\n    [18] => created_by\r\n    [19] => creation_date\r\n    [20] => last_update_by\r\n    [21] => last_update_date</pre>','CONTENT'),(162,'<p>All three are language construct (not functions). The functionality & usage of die/exit is same. You use both to completely stop the program from executing further.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p> <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Die/Exit</strong></span><br />1.    Program stop as soon as the die/exit is reached.<br />2.    Program won’t read/execute any codes/files included after these statements.<br />3.    You can show a message by putting it in parentheses of die/exit.<br />Ex: exit(\"The status of process further is ($process_further)!\");<br /><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Return</strong></span><br />Return can be used in a function, eval() statement or file.<br />1.    In a function, it stops the execution of the functions and returns the ‘Return statement argument’ as returned value.<br />2.    In an included file, it stops the execution of the file where it’s used and goes back to the original file from where it was included.<br />3.    In an eval() stamen, it stop the execution of the statement.</p>\r\n</blockquote>','PHP'),(165,'<p>Including files in a referenced file<br />Including a file in php is easy.<br /><br />1. File in same directory<br />Inclue_once ‘file_name.php’;<br /><br />2. File in one upper level directory<br />include_once(\"../file_name.inc\")<br /><br />3. File in two upper level directory<br /> include_once(\"../../../file_name.inc\")<br /><br />But including a file which is called in from another file is tricky.<br />Ex: filea.php includes a file as<br />include_once(\"../../../fileb.inc\")<br /><br />Now suppose fileb needs to include another file which is in one level up from it then you can’t write<br />include_once(\"../filec.inc\").<br /><br />This means you are trying to access the file fileb from one level up from the directory where the original file filea resides<br />You have to use dirname(__FILE__) or __DIR__  to include file c<br />include(dirname(__FILE__).\'/../filec.inc\');</p>','PHP'),(197,'<p>inoERP is an open source php based enterprise management system. The ERP systems contain all the required modules for running a SME manufacturing/distribution organization. The features are very similar to Oracle R12/ Fusion Application and SAP. It also contains a light weight CMS which seamlessly integrates with the ERP<br /><br /> <br />Below are the fully functional ERP Modules available in inoERP 100. General Ledger (GL)<br /><br />100.1 A multi segment chart of account structure to represent all the segments of a business. Ex : 001-100-1020202-0100-100 Where 001 – Represents a specific company / business unit /legal entity 100 – Represents a cost center 1020202 – a Natural account such as Asset, Liability, Expense, Income or Owners Equity<br /><br />100.2 Calendars Define as many different finical calendars as required Ex : One calendar INO_CORP for Corporate and INO_USA, INO_UK for specific countries<br /><br />100.3 Account Combinations 100.4 Currency & Conversions 100.5 Ledger : A set of calendar, currency and accounts 100.6 Banks 100.6.1 Internal Banks 100.6.2 External Banks – Supplier & Customer 100.7 Journal 100.7.1 Manual Journal Entry 100.7.2 Upload Journals from Excel 100.7.3 Validate & Post Sub ledger Journal Entries<br /><br />    Accounts Payable(AP) 101.1 Suppliers 101.2 AP Transactions 101.2.1 Invoices 101.2.2 Debit Memo 101.2.3 Credit Memo 101.2.4 Prepayment 101.3 PO Matching<br /><br />2.3.1 Multi select matching 101.4 AP Payments 101.4.1 Single Invoice Payment 101.4.2 Multi select Payment 101.5 Transfer Journals to GL<br /><br />    Accounts Receivable(AR) 102.1 Customer 102.2 AR Transactions 102.2.1 Invoices 102.2.2 Debit Memo 102.2.3 Credit Memo 102.2.4 Deposit 102.2.5 Guarantee 102.2.6 Charge Back 102.3 AR Payments 102.3.1 Single Invoice Payment 102.3.2 Multi select Payment 102.4 Transfer Journals to GL<br /><br />    Organizations(ORG) 200.1 Enterprise Org 200.2 Legal Org 200.3 Business Org 200.4 Inventory Org 200.5 Address<br /><br />    Inventory (INV) 201.1 Item Master 201.2 Unit of Measure 201.3 Sub inventory 201.4 Locator 201.5 Inventory Transactions 201.6 Material Receipts 201.6.1 PO Receipt 201.6.2 IR Receipt 201.6.3 RMA Receipt 201.7 Onhand Value 201.8 Cycle Count 201.9 Physical Inventory<br /><br />    Purchasing (PO) 202.1 Purchase Order 202.2 Requisitions 202.3 RFQ 202.4 PO Transactions 202.4.1 PO Receipt Corrections 202.4.2 Return to Supplier 202.4.3 Receipt 202.4.4 Delivery<br /><br />    Sales & Distributions (SD) 203.1 Sales Order 203.2 Sales Picking 203.3 Delivery & Shipment<br /><br />    Bills Of Material (BOM 204.1 Departments 204.2 Resources 204.3 Routing 204.4 BOM 204.5 Super BOM<br /><br />    Costing (CST) 205.1 Material Element 205.2 Material OH 205.3 Overhead 205.4 Resources 205.5 Standard Cost 205.6 Cost Roll Up 205.7 Cost Update<br /><br />    Work in Process (WIP) 206.1 Work Order 206.2 WIP Move Transactions 206.3 WIP Resource Transactions 206.4 WIP Material Transaction 206.5 WO Completion/Return<br /><br />    Supply Chain Planning (SCP) 207.1 Automated Kanban 207.2 Flexibility Planning 207.3 MRP 207.4 Min-Max Planning<br /><br />    Options<br /><br />    Value Groups<br />    Transaction Types<br />    Custom Reporting<br />    Search<br />    Multi Select<br />    Mass Upload<br /><br />Below are the functionalities available in CMS 1. User 2. Blocks 3. Contents – 3.1 Documents 3.2 Forums 3.3 Issue Logs 4. User Roles 5. Role Based Access Control 6. Content Types – To create custom content types</p>',NULL),(198,'<p>All Organizations are classified into 4 differnt groups</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>1. EnterPrise Organization</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>2. Legal Organization</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>3. Business Organization</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>4. Inventory Organization</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"> </p>\r\n<p><strong>1. EnterPrise Organization</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enterrpise is the higest level in the organization hirearhcy. The corporate HQs are usually reprsented by Enterprise.</p>\r\n<p>Ex : inoERP Corp</p>\r\n<p>Enterprise Organization is the organization which is responsible for all the child legal organizations, JVs in differnt countries.</p>\r\n<p><strong>2. Legal Organization</strong></p>\r\n<p>An legal organization is a specific country registered as per the company law of that country. Legal organizations are resposible for maintaing all the statutory requirements in their respective countires. Legal Orgs own employees, assets and responsible for the ownership of the business activities.</p>\r\n<p>Ex : inoERP SPG, inoERP UK, inoERP IND all reporting to inoERP Corp</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong>3. Business Organization</strong></p>\r\n<p>Business organizations are reponsible for daily operational activites. All the extarnal entities such as suppliers, customers directly work with business organizations.</p>\r\n<p>Ex : inoERP SPG - Electronics Division, inoERP SPG - HiTech Division</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong>4. Inventory Organization</strong></p>\r\n<p>Business organizations are reponsible for daily operational activites. All the extarnal entities such as suppliers, customers directly work with business organizations.</p>\r\n<p>Ex : inoERP SPG - Electronics Division, inoERP SPG - HiTech Division</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>',NULL),(199,'<p>Address represents a physical postal addres. Addresses cane be associated with</p>\r\n<p>1. Organization - Enterprise, Legal, Business & Inventory</p>\r\n<p>2. Customers - Customer HQ, Each Sites of the customer</p>\r\n<p>3. Suppliers- Supplier HQ, Each Sites of the supplier</p>\r\n<p>4. Employees</p>\r\n<p>5. Tax organizations</p>\r\n<p> </p>',NULL),(200,'<p>Inventory modules has below features</p>\r\n<p><br />1. Item Master<br />Allows defining items in a master organization and then controlling the item attributes in different organizations.</p>\r\n<p>2. Unit of Measure<br />System allows to setup different unit of measures as per the business requirements. UOM conversion is used for tracking & transacting materials in different UOMs</p>\r\n<p>3. Sub inventory<br />Sub inventory is used to segregate physical areas in shipping/receiving dock, warehouse and production area</p>\r\n<p>4. Locator</p>\r\n<p>5. On hand</p>\r\n<p>6. Inventory Transactions</p>\r\n<p>7. Inventory Receipts</p>',NULL),(207,'<p>Customer is an external/internal organization who buys good, product or service from another organization.  inoERP customer module supports all the functionalities required to create/manage & maintain different type of customer relationships  .</p>\r\n<p>You can<br />1.    Enter multiple physical addresses as different customer sites for a single customer.<br />2.    Assign & Use the same customer in different business units.<br />3.    Assign a business purpose for each address. Such as Ship to, Bill to.<br />4.    Define contact people, bank accounts, payment methods, telephone numbers, and relationships for each customer. <br />5.    Manage all tax and legally required customer information.<br />6.    Default transaction information such as price list , payment term, FOB and attachments from customer</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"files/temp/1402750383_ar_customer.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"900\" height=\"397\" /></p>',NULL),(208,'<p>inoERP provides different planning methods to satisfy different business requirements</p>\r\n<p>1.    Material Requirement Planning :<br />MRP is an old, traditional, push based production planning and inventory control system used to manage manufacturing processes. The biggest drawback of MRP is that it’s a push based system and doesn’t quickly respond to demand/supply variations.<br /><br />inoERP MRP works like any other MRP based system. It takes input from forecast, BOM, sales order & work orders. System does a complete BOM explosion and then determines the requirement for each item using offset and netting. MRP suggests orders for purchasing & production.<br /><br />2.    Min Max Planning:<br />Min Max is a very simple but effective material replenishment method. For each item, you specify minimum and maximum inventory levels in an organization or subinvntory (subinvntory level MinMax is not yet fully functional). When the inventory level for an item drops below the minimum, system suggests a new requisition or work order to bring the balance back up to the maximum.<br /><br />The major limitation with Min Max is that it’s a simple two bin system. So the average inventory hold can be very high for long lead time items. This issue is resolved by Multi Bin Min Max Planning.<br /><br />3.    Multi-Bin Min Max Planning<br />4.    Automated Kanban System</p>',NULL),(209,'<p>1. Supplier</p>\r\n<p>2. Requisition</p>\r\n<p>3. Purchase Order</p>\r\n<p>4. PO Receving</p>\r\n<p>5. PO Return</p>\r\n<p>6. Invoice Matching</p>',NULL),(210,'<p>Work In Procsss</p>',NULL),(211,'<p>Bills Of Material</p>',NULL),(212,'<p>Work Order</p>',NULL),(213,'<p>Routing</p>',NULL),(216,'<p>Sales module has following functionalities</p>\r\n<p>1. Creating Sales Order<br />    manually creates or Import external sales order. Auto generate internal sales order</p>\r\n<p>2. Book Order<br />    Auto book the sales order on basis of available to promise</p>\r\n<p>3. Pick Order<br />    Pick & Consolidate different orders/lines for a single delivery</p>\r\n<p>4. Ship Order<br />    Ship sales order to reduce inventory, generate COGS and print required shipping documents</p>\r\n<p>5. Price List<br />    price List allows defaulting prices for sales order on basis of different criteria</p>\r\n<p>6. Invoice Order<br />    Auto generate receivable invoices after sales completion</p>',NULL),(217,'<p>Receivable module has following functionalities</p>\r\n<p>1. Transaction<br />Create various types of transactions such as Invoice, Debit Memo, Credit Memo, Deposit & Guarantee.<br />Auto create transaction on basis of sales order shipment or RMA receipt<br />Load invoices from excel</p>\r\n<p>2. Tax <br />Define and apply different taxes as per requirement</p>\r\n<p>3. Receipt<br />Create receipts and apply to transactions</p>\r\n<p>4. Multi-Receipt<br />Import receipts from bank transactions and auto apply to transactions</p>',NULL),(218,'<p>Supplier module has following functionalities</p>\r\n<p>1. Supplier<br />Create external & internal suppliers for purchasing goods & services. Employees can be defined as internal supplier for expense claims</p>\r\n<p>2. Supplier Sites<br />Create multiple supplier sites to represent different physical location/supplier entities. Supplier & sites are created in a global level and available for all business uints</p>\r\n<p>3. Supplier-BU Relationship<br />Segregate the supplier BU relationship in business unit level to maintain different bank accounts and tracking separate liability<br /><br /></p>',NULL),(219,'<p>General Ledger module has following functionalities<br />Below are the fully functional ERP Modules available in inoERP 100. General Ledger (GL)<br /><br />1. Chart of Account<br />a multi segment chart of account structure to represent all the segments of a business.<br /> Ex : 001-100-1020202-0100-100<br /> Where 001 – Represents a specific company / business unit /legal entity <br />100 – Represents a cost center <br />1020202 – a Natural account such as Asset, Liability, Expense, Income or Owners Equity<br /><br />2. Calendars<br /> Define as many different finical calendars as required as per business requirements<br /> Ex : One calendar INO_CORP for Corporate and INO_USA, INO_UK for specific countries<br /><br />3. Account Combinations<br />4. Currency & Conversions <br />5. Ledger<br /> A set of calendar, currency and accounts<br />6. Banks <br />Internal Banks. External Banks – Supplier & Customer<br />7. Journal <br />Manual Journal Entry <br />Upload Journals from Excel <br />Validate & Post Sub ledger Journal Entries</p>',NULL),(220,'<p>Purchasing module has following features</p>\r\n<p>1.    Requisitions<br />Create manual requisition or generate requisitions from any planning engine – MRP, MinMax or MMM</p>\r\n<p>2.    Purchase <br />Create standard, blanket and global blanket agreements</p>\r\n<p>3.    Receiving/Return<br />Receive materials against PO through direct receipt or after inspection</p>\r\n<p>4.    Sourcing Rule</p>\r\n<p>5.    Request for quotation</p>\r\n<p>6.    Quotation</p>',NULL),(221,'<p>Payable module has following features</p>\r\n<p>1.    Transactions<br />Create various transactions such invoice, debit memo, credit memo, expense report, pre-payment etc</p>\r\n<p>2.    Tax <br />Define & apply various taxes as per business requirements</p>\r\n<p>3.    Payment</p>\r\n<p>4.    Multi-Payment</p>\r\n<p>5.    Invoice Matching</p>\r\n<p>6.    Accounting</p>',NULL),(233,'<p>TESTing again for documentation</p>','CONTENT'),(236,'<p>sdfsdfsdf</p>',NULL),(240,'<p>All Inventory & non-inventory items are managed in item master sub module of inventory module. Inventory items are those which exist physically where as non-inventory items are defined primarily for sales & purchasing activates but not tracked as on hand inventory.</p>\r\n<p>Examples of non-inventory items are services, warranty & subscriptions.</p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><strong>Item Attributes</strong></span></h3>\r\n<p>Item attributes are item related information that you need to enter in the system for tracking & transaction purposes. All the item attributes are grouped into different modules /sub-modules in the item master form for easy data entry.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"files/temp/1420434052_item_master.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"310\" /></p>\r\n<p>inoERP has many seeded (150+) item attributes used standard businesses, and it also allows you create new attributes through an extra field functionality. Extra fields can be used for any business specific important field that’s not seeded in inoERP. Once defined and implemented, extra fields looks and behave in the same way as any other seeded attribute field.</p>\r\n<p>You use the Item Master form to add, update, search, and maintain item data. <br />Item master form allows any number of file attachments.<br />Item master form allows any number of notes entry.</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 11px;\">Item master navigation</span><span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"font-size: 11px; white-space: pre;\"> <br /></span></strong>You can access item master through system menu or from dashboard<br />1. System Menu <br />2. Roll mouse over INV<br />3. Click on Item Master<br /><span style=\"font-size: 11px;\">Or,<br />1. Dashboard <br /></span>2. Click on Inventory<br />3.Click on Item Master. </p>\r\n<p> </p>','CONTENT'),(262,'&lt;h2&gt;Default Home Page !&lt;/h2&gt;This is the default home page for inoERP. You can change/delete this page from your dashboard. \r\nTo view dashboard , Click on the login button on the right top corner , and use the default username  and password  ( inoerp/inoerp or admin/admin)\r\nYou can read the documentations @ &lt;a href=&quot; http://inoideas.org/content.php?content_type=documentation&amp;amp;category_id=30&quot;&gt; http://inoideas.org/content.php?content_type=documentation&amp;amp;amp;amp;category_id=30&lt;/a&gt;\r\n',NULL),(275,'You can create one or more payment line for each payment header. Payment line contains the transaction information against which the payment is prepared.\r\n&lt;img src=&quot;http://inoideas.org/files/temp/1431234521_Payment_Line.PNG&quot; class=&quot;img-responsive&quot;&gt;\r\n&lt;strong&gt;Sequence Number:&lt;/strong&gt;\r\nSequence number is a read-only field. System auto-populates a unique sequence number for all the lines across all the tabs for easy viewing of data of a single line in different tabs.\r\n\r\n&lt;strong&gt;Line Id:&lt;/strong&gt;\r\nLine id is a read-only field. Line id is an auto increased, primary key of the ap_payment_line table.\r\n\r\n&lt;strong&gt;Transaction Id: &lt;/strong&gt;\r\nTransaction id is a read-only field and defaults from the transaction number.\r\n\r\n&lt;strong&gt;Transaction Number: &lt;/strong&gt;\r\nSelect transaction number against which the payment is being prepared.\r\n\r\n&lt;strong&gt;Payment Amount:&lt;/strong&gt;\r\nEnter payment amount. Payment amount should be less than equal remaining amount.\r\n\r\n&lt;strong&gt;Rate:&lt;/strong&gt;\r\nRate field defaults from the exchange rate from the header.\r\n\r\n&lt;strong&gt;GL Amount:&lt;/strong&gt;\r\nGL amount is read-only field. System calculates GL amount by multiplying payment amount with the rate.\r\nGL Amount = Payment Amount * Rate.\r\n\r\n&lt;strong&gt;Total Amount:&lt;/strong&gt;\r\nTotal amount shows the total transaction amount. Total amount is a read-only field.\r\n\r\n&lt;strong&gt;Paid Amount:&lt;/strong&gt;\r\nPaid amount shows the total amount paid for the selected transaction. Paid amount is read-only field. \r\n\r\n&lt;strong&gt;Remaining Amount:&lt;/strong&gt;\r\nRemaining amount shows the total remaining amount of the selected transaction. Remaining amount is a read-only field. System calculates the remaining amount by subtracting paid amount from the total amount.\r\nRemaining Amount = Total Amount &ndash; Paid Amount. \r\n',NULL),(276,'&lt;?php  echo \'hello\' ?&gt;\r\n&lt;h2&gt;sdfsd &lt;/h2&gt;\r\n&lt;br&gt;sdf\r\nsdf\r\nsdfsdf',NULL);
